   <abstract>This report details the cuts made by the House of Representatives in 1994 that conbtributed to major decrease in services to poor children and families. $30 billion were stripped from crucial child survival programs like SSI (Supplemental Security Income), AFDC (Aid to Families with Dependent Children), Foster Care and Adoption Assistance, the School Lunch Program, Child Care, Services to Disabled, Abused, and Neglected Children, and Child and Adult Food Program.</abstract>
